02/02/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- A NATO team plans to visit Macedonia next week to assess the pace of reforms, Defence Minister Jovan Manasievski said on Wednesday (1 February). 
The talks will focus on implementation of measures aimed at restructuring the armed forces, as well as constitutional and judicial reforms. 
Manasievski added that he expects a generally positive evaluation.
In other news Wednesday, Norway donated 200,000 euros to the defence ministry for a centre to support the social reintegration of laid-off military staff. 
The funding will be used for equipment and training programmes. 
(Macedonian Government Web site - 02/02/06; A1 TV - 01/02/06)
